text: Bobel Cay is an island in Honduras, located around 500km off its east coast. ==Location== One of the most southerly islands in Honduras, the cay is located close to the border of Nicaragua and Honduras. In 2007, the International Court of Justice rules that Bobel Cay and three other islands were within the lawful jurisdiction of Honduras. ==References== Category:Caribbean islands of Honduras
title: Bobel Cay
